2.4. Sample Size and Composition
In this study, we used purposive sampling to survey questionnaire answers face-to-face in
Taichung city, Taiwan. We distributed 408 survey forms and 100% of these were returned. After
eliminating 92 invalid survey forms, 316 valid survey forms remained for a valid return rate of 77.45%.
Regarding the respondents’ demographics, slightly fewer were women than men (41.1%versus 58.9%).
The largest age group among the respondents were those aged 31–40 years (38.4%), followed by
41–50 years (31.5%). The most common highest level of educational achievement was senior high
school (42.5%), followed by university (30.6%). Over half of the respondents worked in the service
industry (38.6%) or the traditional manufacturing industry (22.8%). The average monthly income
